description:
Implement RendererSpec - the seed specification for renderers before they're compiled into a PromptWorld.

Location: crates/baml-bridge/src/prompt/renderer.rs

```rust
/// Specification for a renderer (pre-compilation)
pub enum RendererSpec {
    /// Jinja template source
    Jinja {
        source: &'static str,
    },
    /// Function-based renderer
    Func {
        f: fn(&PromptValue, &RenderSession) -> RenderResult,
    },
}

/// Container for collected renderer specs from registry
#[derive(Debug, Default)]
pub struct RendererDbSeed {
    pub specs: IndexMap<RendererKey, RendererSpec>,
}

impl RendererDbSeed {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self { specs: IndexMap::new() }
    }

    pub fn insert(&mut self, key: RendererKey, spec: RendererSpec) {
        self.specs.insert(key, spec);
    }
}
```

Note: RendererSpec uses &'static str for Jinja source because templates come from proc-macro attributes which are compile-time constants.

The fn pointer signature references PromptValue and RenderSession which will be defined later - use forward declarations or place this after those types.

# Purpose

Update the Module trait and optimizers to work with typed Predict<S> via BamlValue interchange.

## Why This Is Optional/Later

1. Optimizers are complex, touching many files
2. Legacy Predict + MetaSignature can continue working
3. Typed API is user-facing; optimizers are internal
4. Can be done as follow-up after core integration is stable

## Current Module Trait

```rust
pub trait Module: Send + Sync {
    async fn forward(&self, inputs: Example) -> Result<Prediction>;
}
```

## Target Module Trait

```rust
pub trait Module: Send + Sync {
    /// Untyped forward for optimizer compatibility.
    async fn forward_untyped(&self, input: BamlValue) -> Result<BamlValue, PredictError>;

    /// Signature specification for introspection.
    fn signature_spec(&self) -> &dyn SignatureSpec;
}
```

## Implementation for Predict<S>

```rust
impl<S: Signature> Module for Predict<S>
where
    S::Input: ToBamlValue,
    S: ToBamlValue,
{
    async fn forward_untyped(&self, input: BamlValue) -> Result<BamlValue, PredictError> {
        // Convert BamlValue -> S::Input
        let typed_input = <S::Input as BamlValueConvert>::try_from_baml_value(input, vec![])
            .map_err(|e| PredictError::Conversion { source: e.into(), parsed: BamlValue::Null })?;

        // Call typed API
        let result = self.call(typed_input).await?;

        // Convert S -> BamlValue
        Ok(result.to_baml_value())
    }

    fn signature_spec(&self) -> &dyn SignatureSpec {
        // Return trait object with S::input_fields(), S::output_fields()
    }
}
```

## Migration Path

1. Keep legacy Module trait and impl for legacy Predict
2. Add Module impl for Predict<S> using BamlValue
3. Update optimizers to use forward_untyped
4. Eventually deprecate legacy

